HEADWORD: parallel-park
<hw>parallel-park</hw> <pos>v. t. & i.</pos> <def>To park (a vehicle)
parallel to the curb; -- contrasted with <contr>angle-park</contr>;
<as>as, to get a driver's license, one needs to be able to
parallel-park</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
